cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.CY, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the need for organizations to develop a strong understanding of the risks imposed on their company and the security solutions designed to prevent/minimize vulnerabilities. This suggests that the paper is related to computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the need to create all-inclusive network/security policies, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the need to select standards to prevent unauthorized access, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and security and privacy (cs.SI).
